rComments: I had Prof. Desai for the study abroad trip in Mumbai, India. She's incredibly intelligent and a very nice person, but she was a bit of a taskmaster in not allowing us to have much free time (instead of exploring the city, we had to read tons of articles).
she is the worst teacher in the world, she has no common sense and no teaching abilities

I had professor Desai when she was teaching at HWS. In my intro class, almost everybody was failing. The entire class complained to the dean.  The result was her not coming back, and us all getitng a c.  I went on to be a sociology major with a 3.1 GPA, yet i couldnt pass her intro class.

She is very confusing. She tries to make a lecture of 200 people like a small discussion, doesn't allow people to go to the bathroom, and is very often rude. She does bring up very good points and ideas during lecture, but I often leave lecture wondering what I was supposed to learn.

She is an okay teacher. The only complaint I have is that she is not that clear at all. She expects us to read 80 pages every couple of days, and know everything. The tests have nothing to do with what she says in class. Stay away from her if ever possibl
